--- DEPLOY_INVARIANT ---
NO_DEV_SERVER. Built dist/ is what users see.
ALWAYS: cd client && npm run build && cd .. && firebase deploy --only hosting
Functions change: firebase deploy --only functions
User saying "변경이 안 보여요" = forgot build+deploy.

--- ARCHITECTURE ---
NO_BACKEND. Client-only + Cloud Functions.
Auth: Firebase Auth (Google popup only) + custom Firestore members collection.
  google_uid links Firebase Auth <-> members doc. Not using Firebase Auth for session.
  Session state = localStorage (LS.* constants from lib/storageKeys.ts). NEVER hardcode key strings.
  After login: await recordLogin(id) THEN window.location.reload(). Order matters — reload kills pending Firestore writes.

Admin: single members doc where is_admin:true. AdminView is separate route.
  Admin google_email shown to users as contact → useAdminEmail() hook (hooks/useAdminEmail.ts).
  3 components use this hook: HelpView, MyMenuView, FamilyGroupRequestScreen.

Routing: all in App.tsx. No react-router. Conditional returns based on localStorage + React state.
  FamilyGroupRequestScreen triggers when: !hasFamilyId OR (persons empty AND hasFamilyId).
  hard-refresh safe: useEffect checks !hasFamilyId BEFORE awaiting loading.

--- KEY_FILES ---
App.tsx: routing hub, auth state, android back-intercept (backPressedRef+toast), applyMemberLogin (MUST await recordLogin before reload)
store/familyStore.ts: ALL Firestore CRUD. Components only touch store, never Firestore directly (except dynamic imports in a few admin ops).
hooks/useTreeLayout.ts: getChusu(BFS촌수), classifyBranch(4계통), canSeeFull(가시성), layout engine. Wide blast radius — touch carefully.
functions/src/index.ts: 3 functions: onInfoRequestCreated(FCM trigger), sendAnniversaryReminders(hourly+KST check), cleanupLoginLogs(monthly 1yr purge)
lib/storageKeys.ts: LS.* and SS.* — always use these, never raw strings.
sw.ts: Service Worker. Background FCM handling.

--- COLLECTIONS ---
persons, relationships, members, invites, approval_requests, info_requests, info_access, person_access_pairs, login_logs, settings/push(single doc)

settings/push schema: {sendHourKST:number, offsets:number[], maxChusu:number, enableBirthday:bool, enableDeathDay:bool}
  Functions read this at runtime. Admin UI writes it. No redeploy needed to change push behavior.

members schema adds: last_login_at(ISO), fcm_token, google_uid, google_email, is_admin(bool)

--- PATTERNS_CRITICAL ---
# Admin email fetch — use hook, not inline:
import { useAdminEmail } from '../hooks/useAdminEmail';
const adminEmail = useAdminEmail();

# Login flow completion:
await recordLogin(member.id).catch(() => {});
window.location.reload(); // must come after

# ReactFlow NodeProps data cast (intentional double-cast, TS requires it):
data as unknown as PersonNodeData  // NOT: data as PersonNodeData (won't compile)

# Dynamic imports pattern (used in admin ops to avoid bundle bloat):
const { setDoc, doc } = await import('firebase/firestore');
const { db: fdb } = await import('../lib/firebase');

# Date format used in admin UI: YYMMDD hh:mm
function fmtDt(iso: string, withTime = true) — defined top of AdminView.tsx

